data.enText: argument/idea/plan
to refuse to accept or consider sth

data.chText: 拒绝接受一个论点 / 一项要求 / 一个决定 / 一项提议 / 一个建议
data.enText: to reject an argument/a claim/a decision/an offer/a suggestion

data.chText: 首相对任何改革体制的想法都不予考虑。
data.enText: The prime minister rejected any idea of reforming the system.
The proposal was firmly rejected .

data.chText: 我们所有的建议都被一口拒绝了。
data.enText: All our suggestions were rejected out of hand .
sb for job
to refuse to accept sb for a job, position, etc.
Please reject the following candidates…

data.chText: 所有我申请的大学都没有录取我。
data.enText: I've been rejected by all the universities I applied to.
not use/publish

data.chText: （因质量差）不用，不出售，不出版
data.enText: to decide not to use, sell, publish, etc. sth because its quality is not good enough

data.chText: 我们严把质量关，有问题的文章都被退回。
data.enText: Imperfect articles are rejected by our quality control.
new organ
to not accept a new organ after a transplant operation, by producing substances that attack the organ
not love
to fail to give a person or an animal enough care or affection

data.chText: 母狮排斥最小的幼狮，把它饿死了。
data.enText: The lioness rejected the smallest cub, which died.

data.chText: 丈夫离家后，她觉得遭到了抛弃而且无能为力。
data.enText: When her husband left home she felt rejected and useless.

data.chText: 她的建议遭到一致否决。
data.enText: Her proposal met with unanimous rejection.
a rejection letter (= a letter in which you are told, for example, that you have not been accepted for a job)
painful feelings of rejection
sth that cannot be used
something that cannot be used or sold because there is sth wrong with it
person

data.chText: 不合格者；被剔除者；被拒收者
data.enText: a person who has not been accepted as a member of a team, society, etc.
one of society's rejects

simple_means.memory_skill: re 回 + ject 投掷，扔 → 扔回来 → 拒绝

ex.enText: He was denied entry to the country.

synonyms.bx: 指不允许某人拥有某物或做某事。

ex.chText: 我夫人谢绝了格林太太的晚宴邀请。
ex.enText: My wife declined Mrs. Green's invitation to dinner.

ex.chText: 布朗先生虽然很穷，却谢绝了慈善团体的一大笔捐款。
ex.enText: Poor as he was, Mr. Brown declined a large sum of money from the charity.

ex.chText: 我们同意让他搭车，但是他却谢绝了。
ex.enText: We agreed to offer him a lift but he declined.

synonyms.bx: 指婉言谢绝他人的帮助、邀请等。

ex.chText: 她断然拒绝了他所有的友好表示。
ex.enText: She rebuffed all his offers of friendship.

synonyms.bx: 指很不友好地拒绝别人善意的建议或帮助。

ex.chText: 她拒绝一个人到那里去。
ex.enText: She refused to go there alone.

ex.chText: 她叫他一起来，但是他拒绝了。
ex.enText: She asked him to come with her, but he refused.
He refused a second cup of coffee.

ex.chText: 这个建议太好了，让人难以拒绝。
ex.enText: The suggestion seems too good to refuse/turn down.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指拒绝做某事或接受别人所给之物，作后者解时常可与turn down 换用。

ex.chText: 他对要求他辞职的呼声置之不理。
ex.enText: He rejected calls for his resignation.

ex.chText: 我弟弟因为视力不好未能参军。
ex.enText: My brother was rejected by the army because of his poor eyesight.

synonyms.bx: 指拒绝接受或考虑某事，或指由于不能让人满意而不接受、不录取等。

tr: the person or thing that is rejected or set aside as inferior in quality
dismiss from consideration or a contest
example: John was ruled out as a possible suspect because he had a strong alibi
This possibility can be eliminated from our consideration
I reject the idea of starting a war
The journal rejected the student's paper
I disapprove of her child rearing methods
He refused my offer of hospitality
They turned away hundreds of fans
Black people were often rejected by country clubs

tr: resist immunologically the introduction of some foreign tissue or organ
example: His body rejected the liver of the donor

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /rɪ'dʒekt/. The noun is pronounced /'riːdʒekt/. 动词读作/rɪ'dʒekt/。名词读作/'riːdʒekt/。

value.def: If you reject something such as a proposal, a request, or an offer, you do not accept it or you do not agree to it.

example.ex: The British government is expected to reject the idea of state subsidy for a new high speed railway...
example.tran: 预计英国政府不会考虑为修建一条新的高速铁路提供国家补贴的设想。

example.ex: Seventeen publishers rejected the manuscript before Jenks saw its potential.
example.tran: 17家出版社回绝了这部手稿，直到詹克斯看到了它的潜在价值。

value.tran: 拒绝考虑;不接受;不同意

example.ex: The rejection of such initiatives indicates that voters are unconcerned about the environment.
example.tran: 此类倡议遇冷表明选民对环境并不关心。

value.def: If you reject a belief or a political system, you refuse to believe in it or to live by its rules.

example.ex: ...the children of Eastern European immigrants who had rejected their parents' political and religious beliefs.
example.tran: 抛弃了父母一代政治和宗教信仰的东欧移民子女

value.tran: 摈弃，抛弃，不接受(信仰或政治制度)

example.tran: 他对我们的价值观的摒弃

value.def: If someone is rejected for a job or course of study, it is not offered to them.

example.ex: One of my most able students was rejected by another university.
example.tran: 我的一个最有能力的学生申请另一所大学落选了。

example.ex: Be prepared for lots of rejections before you land a job.
example.tran: 在找到一份工作之前，要做好屡次碰壁的准备。

value.def: If someone rejects another person who expects affection from them, they are cold and unfriendly towards them.

example.ex: You make friends with people and then make unreasonable demands so that they reject you.
example.tran: 你和别人交朋友，然后向人家提出无理要求，结果被人家拒绝。

example.ex: ...people who had been rejected by their lovers.
These feelings of rejection and hurt remain.
example.tran: 被拒绝和受伤的感觉还在。

value.def: If a person's body rejects something such as a new heart that has been transplanted into it, it tries to attack and destroy it.

example.ex: It was feared his body was rejecting a kidney he received in a transplant four years ago.
example.tran: 令人担心的是，他的身体可能对4年前移植的肾产生了排斥反应。

value.tran: 排斥(移植器官)；对…产生排斥反应

example.ex: ...a special drug which stops rejection of transplanted organs.
example.tran: 一种可以阻止身体对移植器官产生排异反应的特殊药物

value.def: If a machine rejects a coin that you put in it, the coin comes out and the machine does not work.
A reject is a product that has not been accepted for use or sale, because there is something wrong with it.
